cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is likely because the paper considers a task graph mapped on a set of processors, which suggests a distributed or parallel computing setting. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely because the paper deals with dynamic voltage and frequency scaling (DVFS), which is a control technique used to optimize the energy consumption of a system. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category because the paper aims at minimizing the energy consumption while enforcing a prescribed bound on the execution time (makespan), which is a performance metric. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is another possible category because the paper considers different speed models for the processors, which is related to the architecture of the computing system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible because the paper proposes several scheduling heuristics and assesses their complexity.
